The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | HC nudge on Dhoni dispute
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      HC nudge on Dhoni dispute
          OUR BUREAU                              
	The high court on Friday asked Mahendra Singh Dhoni and city-based sports management company Gameplan to settle their dispute over the sharing of advertisement proceeds through bipartite discussion or arbitration. The Team India skipper had moved the court in April, seeking an order for Gameplan to pay him Rs 8.8 crore. Dhoni had accused the company of violating an advertisement deal and underpaying him.        
	Traffic fine: Traffic offenders can now pay their fines through any branch of the UBI following an agreement between the bank and the traffic police. Earlier, the fines could be paid only at 36 branches of the bank in the city.        
	Diesel subsidy: Transport minister Ranjit Kundu announced on Friday at the Writers Buildings that the state government was considering paying the subsidy of Rs 2 per litre of diesel to transporters from August 16. It was earlier decided that the subsidy would be paid from September 1.        
	Power-cut alert: Power supply to parts of the AJC Bose Road, Lenin Sarani, Taltala, Beniapukur, Nonapukur, Mullickbazar, Moulali, Convent Road, Girish Bose Road, Ananda Palit Road, Sambhu Babu Lane, Hazra Bagan Lane, Sealdah, Baithakkhana Road, Bowbazar, Madan Dutta Lane and SN Banerjee Road areas may be affected between 9am and 2pm on Sunday because of maintenance by CESC.        
	Juvenile board: The high court on Friday asked the state government to ensure that the juvenile justice board started functioning from its GC Avenue office within 30 days.        
	Beaten to death: Two alleged criminals, Nayan Ganguly and Rony Chowdhury, died after being assualted by a group at a construction site in Pasupati Bhattacharya Lane in Behala around 9pm on Friday.                                                                                                                                                          
